content.description: Follows small crystals and crimps to a semi high top out. 3/4 of the way up get a decent rest in the horizontal seam that you would think should have jugs. Not as a good of holds as it appears.
content.location: go to the end of the "dead end" corridor. this problem begins to the right of the chockstone.

content.description: Start in the "dead end" corridor. Right at the opening of it. Make a move or two on the face and then finish up the upper part on the ramp feature.
content.location: first problem encountered when coming through the corridor and turning right.

content.description: Starts to the right of the ramp feature. Follows balanced holds to the upper "seam crack".
content.location: Hike up to the Gatekeeper and Addys arete go through the corridor this problem will be on your right as you come to the end of the corridor.

content.description: The best warm up in this area. Again, Looks like it should be a walk up but involves good smearing and keeping a good head.Start on small crystals and go directly up. Make your way up to the horizontal crack 3/4 the way up. If you make it here either fire off the last 2 moves to the top of take a breather.

Corridor warm ups are excellent warm up problems on some of the best granite in the area! Hike up to The gatekeeper and addys arete. Follow the corridor to the left of Addys arete. Go through it and hang a right as it opens up. Obvious lines up this fin!
